      <div class="process-block">
        <h3>&#x2758; Reserach &#x26; Dicovery</h3>
        <div>
          <h6>Project Requirements</h6>
          <p>
            Total Swimming expressed several concerns they had with the usability of the webiste. The usability concerns were as follows;
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>User retention issues</li>
            <li>Sign up rates are dwindling via the site</li>
            <li>A number of complaints about the accessibility of the website</li>
            <li>The conversion of users using mobile phones to access the site is low.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h6>Usability Testing &#x26; Data Analysis Methodoloy</h6>
          <p>
            To gain a well rounded, balanced understanding of Total Swimmings user base, including their goals and intentions for using the service, a mixture of discovery tasks and testing techniques were applied; Usability Testing and Data Analysis.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h6>User Research</h6>
          <p>Data Analyses of the demographical and user flow data of the Google Analytics Data was first conducted which would allow us to further model the users, their demographics and normal customer interaction with the website.</p>
          <p>I created two users types; A new user and a returning user.</p>
